Method code

In[34]:
def count_plot(
    df,
    x_col,
    hue=None, 
    fig_sise=(10, 8), 
    title="", 
    xlabel="x", 
    ylabel="y", 
    color="blue",
    palette="deep"
):
    plt.figure(figsize=fig_sise)
    sns.countplot(data=df, x=x_col, hue=hue, color=color, palette=palette)
    plt.title(title)
    plt.xlabel(xlabel)
    plt.ylabel(ylabel)
    plt.show()


def hist_plot(
    df,
    x_col,
    hue=None, 
    fig_sise=(10, 8), 
    bins=None, 
    kde=False, 
    title="", 
    xlabel="x", 
    ylabel="y", 
    color="blue",
):
    plt.figure(figsize=fig_sise)
    sns.histplot(data=df, x=x_col, hue=hue, bins=bins, kde=kde, color=color)
    plt.title(title)
    plt.xlabel(xlabel)
    plt.ylabel(ylabel)
    plt.show()


def pie_plot(
        df,
        x_col,
        fig_size=(8, 8),
        colors=None
):
    plt.figure(figsize=fig_size)
    df[x_col].value_counts().plot.pie(colors=colors, autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.show()


def get_corr_map(
    df,
    fig_sise=(16, 12),
    fmt='.2g',
    annot=True
):
    plt.figure(figsize=fig_sise)
    sns.heatmap(df.corr(), fmt=fmt, annot=annot)
    plt.show()


def print_value_counts(df, col):
    print(df[col].value_counts())

    "Canada",
    "Mexico",
    "India"

    "Honduras",

    "El-Salvador "

In[50]:
def categorize_countries(country):
    if country in individual_countries:
        return country
    elif country in Europe:
        return "Europe"
    elif country in East_Asia:
        return "East_Asia"
    elif country in Southeast_Asia:
        return "Southeast_Asia"
    elif country in Caribbean_Basin:
        return "Caribbean_Basin"
    elif country in Central_America:
        return "Central_America"
    elif country in South_America:
        return "South_America"
    else:
        return "Other"

for feature in categorical_features:

In[67]:
def transform_data(data, features, encoders):
    for feature in features:
        data[feature] = encoders[feature].transform(data[feature])
In[68]:

Saving coded features

In[73]:
def save_label_encoders_to_yaml(encoders, dir_path):
    serializable_encoders = {}
    for feature, encoder in encoders.items():
        serializable_encoders[feature] = dict(zip(encoder.classes_, encoder.transform(encoder.classes_)))

    for feature, data in serializable_encoders.items():
        path = os.path.join(dir_path, f"{feature}.text")
        with open(path, 'w') as f:
            for key, value in data.items():
                f.write(f'{key}: {value}\n')
        print(f"Successfully saved to file: {path}")

In[86]:
def calc_percentages(classes: dict) -> dict:
    total_elements = sum(classes.values())

    return {cls: f"{(count / total_elements) * 100:.2f}" for cls, count in classes.items()}


def print_data_info(X, y, title=""):
    classes = dict(Counter(y))
    print(f"{title}\nLen: {len(X)}\nClasses: {classes}\nPercantage: {calc_percentages(classes)}")
